<div class="comment" id="comment_70141">


<b>Griff Davies</b><br/>


<span class="sub">Feb 21, 2015   5:54pm</span>
	
	<p><em>In reply to <a href="#comment_70124">Jamie Stephenson</a>:</em> <p>Jamie, you already have the longest version (non LP mix) of 'Pangaea' in the 'Complete Columbia' set. For 'Agharta' you have the shorter LP mix, so you'd need to seek out the Japanese Mastersound edition with serial number SRCS 9128/9 OR SRCS 9720/1 for the longer / non LP mix version. For completeness you may want to get 'Pangaea' in the LP mix as well - look for the SICP 1232/3 edition.
<br />I should mention that the extra music on both long versions is all Mtume's solo conga/beat box spot at the end of the sets, so it might not be considered essential!  Hope that helps.</p></p>
	<p><a class="util" href="#" onclick="replyTo('70141', 'Griff Davies'); return false;">Reply to this</a> <a class="util" href="#" onclick="Element.toggle('admin_comment_70141'); return false;">Admin</a>
